SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
Since \( h(x)=f(x)+g(x) \), we know that \( h(-1)=f(-1)+g(-1)=$f[0]+$g[0]=$h[0] \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
Similarly, \( j(x)= $c f(x) \) tells us that \( j(-1)= $c f(-1) =$c ($f[0])=$j[0] \).  Repeat this process for each entry in the tables in parts (a) - (d).
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BCENTER
\{ begintable(7) \}
\{ row( "\( x \)" , @x ) \}
\{ row( "\( h(x) \)", @h ) \}
\{ row( "\( j(x) \)", @j ) \}
\{ row( "\( k(x) \)", @k ) \}
\{ row( "\( m(x) \)", @m ) \}
\{ endtable() \}
$ECENTER
$BR

END_SOLUTION


      
